rComments: Prof. B was a fantastic lecturer and really cared for her student's success. She was engaging and made the lectures easy to follow. The assignments were also very engaging! 10/10!

Dr. Bolintineanu is one of the best professors I have ever had. Everyone in Digital Humanities agrees that they are in the program because of her. Her lectures are always super interesting, and she has such a passion for what she does. She is always open to providing help and is super accommodating. I would recommend her classes to anyone

She is one of the best professors I've ever had the chance of being taught by at University of Toronto. She is so passionate about digital humanities and encourages you to do something you could enjoy with the required assignments. She is also extremely approachable. LOVE LOVE LOVE HER COURSES.
amazing prof. very caring and great at lecturing
Amazing prof! So knowledgeable and caring. Definitely recommend her class, MST202. Best course I have taken so far!

rComments: Prof. B is so passionate about what she studies and what she teaches that it really shines through her lectures and classes. I would say readings are necessary only because class discussion and tutorials are heavily based on readings, but they are pretty short! There were "mini field trips" and "easy" assignments as well. I really enjoyed the class

Prof Bolintineanu was AWESOME! I took this course in my 1st year and it was nice to be in a small class. The content was interesting, and all assignments were very clear in expectations. Great TA support also. She's a great lecturer, really clear to understand and wants you to succeed! Great experience.
